parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gas tank leaks can cause fuel to spill onto the road, creating a fire hazard and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, fuel leaks can lead to engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and environmental pollution.
symptoms: fuel dripping or leaking from the tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose carburetor cables can cause the engine to run rich or lean, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions. In extreme cases, it can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or strandings.
The failure of the oil sending unit nut can cause the oil pressure sensor to malfunction, leading to inaccurate oil pressure readings, which can result in engine damage or failure.
Corrosion or rust on the vehicle's frame can weaken its structural integrity, compromising the safety of the occupants and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame
visible signs of damage or weakening
unusual noises or vibrations while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilizer link can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and decreased handling, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially during sharp turns or sudden maneuvers.
symptoms: loose or clunking noise from the front suspension
vibration or shimmy in the steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wheel Lock Inoperative and Loose Nuts and Bolts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel lock system and loose nuts and bolts can cause the wheel to detach from the vehicle while in motion, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel lock warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the wheels feel loose or wobbly
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the wheel nuts or bolts are loose or missing.
